data.description: This charming single-family home in Orlando offers a cozy and comfortable living space in a peaceful cul-de-sac location. A brand-new roof that not only enhances its appearance but also provides added protection. The single-car garage is conveniently situated at the front of the house, offering secure parking and additional storage space. Upon entering the home, you'll step into a welcoming foyer that leads to the open-concept living area. The main living space is spacious, well-lit, and perfect for both relaxing and entertaining. This home features three bedrooms, providing ample space for a growing family or accommodating guests. The bedrooms are thoughtfully designed, offering comfort and privacy. Each room has ample natural light and closet space, making them cozy retreats. The two bathrooms in this house are well-appointed, with modern fixtures and finishes. The kitchen is a focal point of the home, plenty of cabinet space, and a functional layout that makes cooking a pleasure. It's also conveniently located, allowing easy access to both the dining area and the living room. Adjacent to the kitchen, you'll find a spacious dining area that can comfortably accommodate a dining table, making it an ideal spot for family meals or gatherings with friends. Situated on a quiet cul-de-sac in Orlando, this home offers a peaceful and safe environment. It's conveniently located near shopping centers, schools, parks, and major highways, providing easy access to all that Orlando has to offer. One notable feature of this property is the absence of a HOA, which means you have more freedom to personalize and use your property as you see fit, without the constraints of HOA rules and fees. In summary, this single-family home in Orlando is a perfect blend of comfort, convenience, and style. With its three bedrooms, two bathrooms, one-car garage, new roof, and cul-de-sac location, it offers a great living experience for individuals or families looking to enjoy the Florida lifestyle without the restrictions of an HOA.
